@startuml C4_Quality_Testing
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Quality Gate - Test Architecture

Boundary(unit_tests, "Unit Tests") {
    Component(util_tests, "UtilityTests", "JUnit", "Helper functions")
    Component(model_tests, "ModelTests", "JUnit", "Domain model")
    Component(service_tests, "ServiceTests", "JUnit", "Service layer")
    Component(coverage_unit, "Coverage: 80%+", "Target", "Line coverage")
}

Boundary(integration_tests, "Integration Tests") {
    Component(db_tests, "DatabaseTests", "Testcontainers", "H2/PostgreSQL")
    Component(api_tests, "APITests", "REST Assured", "HTTP endpoints")
    Component(workflow_tests, "WorkflowTests", "YAWL Engine", "Full workflows")
    Component(coverage_int, "Coverage: 70%+", "Target", "Branch coverage")
}

Boundary(e2e_tests, "End-to-End Tests") {
    Component(scenario_tests, "ScenarioTests", "Chicago TDD", "Real scenarios")
    Component(performance_tests, "PerformanceTests", "JMH", "Benchmarks")
    Component(chaos_tests, "ChaosTests", "Failure injection", "Fault tolerance")
    Component(coverage_e2e, "Coverage: 100%", "Target", "Critical paths")
}

Boundary(ci_integration, "CI/CD Integration") {
    Component(github_actions, "GitHubActions", "CI", "Automated runs")
    Component(test_reporting, "TestReporting", "Reports", "HTML reports")
    Component(coverage_reporting, "CoverageReporting", "Coverage", "Codecov/Sonar")
}

unit_tests --> coverage_unit: Reports
integration_tests --> coverage_int: Reports
e2e_tests --> coverage_e2e: Reports
github_actions --> unit_tests: Runs
github_actions --> integration_tests: Runs
github_actions --> e2e_tests: Runs

Note as N1
Test Strategy (Chicago TDD):

Unit Tests (Fast, Isolated):
- Test individual components
- Mock external dependencies
- Target: 80%+ line coverage
- Execution time: <5 seconds

Integration Tests (Slower, Real):
- Test component interactions
- Use Testcontainers for DB
- Test actual HTTP APIs
- Target: 70%+ branch coverage
- Execution time: <30 seconds

E2E Tests (Slowest, Real World):
- Test complete workflows
- Real data flows
- Scenario-based (user stories)
- Target: 100%+ critical paths
- Execution time: <5 minutes

Fortune 5 Tests (Scale, Real):
- 30 concurrent ARTs
- 5,000+ dependencies
- SLA enforcement (4h, 30m, 15m)
- 65+ test combinations
- Execution time: <4 hours

CI/CD Gates:
1. Compile GREEN
2. Unit tests GREEN
3. Integration tests GREEN
4. E2E tests GREEN
5. Coverage ≥80%
6. All gates must pass before merge
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
